to relax and start your Blaycation countdown.\r\n<strong>SERVICES</strong>\r\nAlthough our clients typically use us for land only programs we are a full service Private Travel Planner. We can assist you or your group with a complete travel itinerary from air, pre tour hotels and transfers. As well as information on immigration, travel visas and other special request and VIP services. Think of Blaycation as your Personal Travel Concierge.\r\n<h3>Bucket List Service</h3>\r\nIf you have always dreamed of flying first class on Emirates or having breakfast at Mt Everest Base Camp or racing a Formula One car in Monaco or flying a hot air balloon above the Serengeti to chartering a private yacht around the Mediterranean, this service is for you. Think of Blaycation as your Personal Travel Concierge.\r\nBlaycation can help you to uncover your personal bucket list experiences and create them especially for you. From, experiential journeys in Asia to the rugged outback of Alaska, or sleeping in an ice hotel under the northern lights. We help you stretch the expanses of your imagination and put them into reality. Come Explore, Dream and Discover with Blaycation.\r\n<h3>Our Team</h3>\r\n<em>Mark Stiles, President &amp; Chief Vacation Officer</em>\r\n\r\nMark’s passion for travel began at a very young age when he was introduced by his parents when they were either travelling or hosting travellers. Mark continued to unlock his passion for travel after University when he spent an entire summer travelling through Europe. After raising his family and running several very successful businesses he continued travelling yearly with his family to tick-off their travel bucket list.\r\n\r\nOnce he realized where he needed to be working, he sold these businesses and started Blaycation, Your Bucket List Vacation. He has now traveled to over 40 countries and when he’s not taking his family on a Greek Island cruise or a Caribbean adventure, you’ll find him passionately seeking-out new luxury travel experiences for his clients worldwide.\r\n\r\nOnce you chat with Mark, it’s not hard to feel his enthusiasm for this industry. Mark believes, deep down, that how you see the World matters. His goal is to help travellers realize their own passions by putting together vacation experiences that go well beyond the trip itself. Mark is very approachable and continues to be hands-on in the business to ensure his clients experiences are Bucket-List Worthy! Mark continues to tick-off his own bucket list while on vacation, and who better to run a company focused-on bucket list vacations!\r\n\r\nHe holds a Bachelor’s degree in Business and Marketing from Acadia University.\r\n\r\n<em>Jamie Little , Vice President - Operations &amp; Private Travel Planner</em>\r\n\r\nJamie has a broad range of professional experience in several different sectors of the travel industry; airline operations, hotel management, meetings and conventions, cruise lines, salmon fishing guiding and over 25-years of planning fully-customized luxury travel around the World. He has travelled to over 80 countries on six continents, including to all 50 of the United States.\r\n\r\nGrowing-up in Vancouver, he was exposed to the excitement of travel at a young age, when his family would go on regular adventures across North America and occasionally, overseas. He caught the \'travel bug\' very early-on; by 6-years old he had memorized every World capital city.\r\n\r\nHe is an expert in the Americas, Europe, Hawaii, Asia and the South Pacific. He also runs the operations for Blaycation and is an accomplished travel writer.\r\n\r\nWhen not working to put together Blaycations for our guests, Jamie can be found on all corners of the globe, often with his young children, uncovering new experiences for our clients.\r\n\r\nJamie majored in Geography at the University of Victoria, in Air Transport Management at Cranfield University in Bedfordshire, UK and subsequently at the Travel and Tourism Management Program at Capilano University in Vancouver.", "About Us", "", "inherit", "closed", "closed", "", "21-revision-v1", "", "", "2015-08-24 01:01:10", "2015-08-24 01:01:10", "", "21", "http://localhost/blaycation/bower_components/wordpress/21-revision-v1/", "0", "revision", "", "0");
